<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" ng-app="application">
    <head>
        <link href="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/images/favicon.ico" rel="shortcut icon">
        <link href="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/bootstrap/docs/assets/css/bootstrap.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <link href="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/bootstrap/docs/assets/css/bootstrap-responsive.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <link href="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/bootstrap-datepicker/css/datepicker.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <link href="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/font-awesome/css/font-awesome.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <link href="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/select2/select2.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <link href="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/stylesheets/all.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <meta charset="utf-8">
        <meta content="IE=edge,chrome=1" http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible">
        <meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" name="viewport">
        <title>{{ module }}</title>
        <!--[if IE 7]>
            <link href="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/font-awesome/css/font-awesome-ie7.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <![endif]-->
    </head>
    <body data-url="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}">
        <div id="top">
            {#
            <a href="http://zonsidekick.com/" class="logo" title="You need help rising to the top of Amazon, we've got you covered.">
                <img alt="Zon Sidekick" src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/images/logo.png">
            </a>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="http://zonsidekick.com/">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://zonsidekick.com/shop/">Shop</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://zonsidekick.com/my-account/">My Account</a></li>
                <li class="active">
                    <a href="{{ url('dashboard') }}">Tools</a>
                    {% if user.id %}
                        <ul>
                            {% if has_kns(groups) %}
                                <li><a href="{{ url('kns_overview') }}">Kindle Niche Sidekick</a></li>
                                <li><a href="{{ url('logos_overview') }}">Logos</a></li>
                            {% endif %}
                            {% if has_aks(groups) %}
                                <li><a href="{{ url('aks') }}">Zon Keyword Sidekick</a></li>
                            {% endif %}
                            <li class="last"><a href="{{ url('feedback') }}">feedback</a></li>
                            <li class="last"><a href="{{ url('profile') }}">Profile</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    {% endif %}
                </li>
                <li><a href="http://zonsidekick.com/intro/">Intro</a></li>
            </ul>
            #}
        </div>
        <div id="middle">
            <div class="container-fluid">
                {% block content %}
                {% endblock %}
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="bottom">
            {#
            <span class="pull-right">
                <a href="http://www.zonsidekick.com/terms">Terms</a>
                <a href="http://www.zonsidekick.com/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a>
            </span>
            <p>Zon Sidekick &copy; 2013. All Rights Reserved.</p>
            #}
        </div>
        <div class="fade hide modal" id="kns-qsg">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <button
                    class="close"
                    type="button"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    data-dismiss="modal"
                    >&times;</button>
                <h3>New User Guide</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <p>Welcome to the Kindle Niche Sidekick new user guide.</p>
                <p>Enter the keywords you wish to analyze in the Keywords box. This box will allow scrolling as more keywords are entered and may be resized for viewing by dragging the handle in the lower right corner.</p>
                <p>When you're ready to analyze, press the green Submit button below the Keywords box. Your report will begin to generate and export options will appear. Please note that the download and email buttons will only become available when your report completes. If you wish to have both the CSV and PDF report e-mailed to you automatically, place a check in the "Automatically email on completion" box. The on-screen report will display information at a "high level" whereas the PDF report will display <strong>very</strong> detailed information. It is highly recommended that you download the PDF report to fully understand our analysis.</p>
                <p><strong>Competition</strong> is calculated by determining the "market type" of each keyword. We've modelled each keyword by analyzing the market share owned by current sellers to determine whether or not the keyword appears to be accessible for new sellers. If 99% of sales within a keyword belong to just one book, the odds of your publication earning money are very low without a major following. Ideal keywords are those in which buyers purchase a variety of books, this typically means there's no definitive "best product" for users searching for that keyword. We recommend choosing keywords with low competition so that your quality books may grab enough sales and reviews to rise to a dominating position.</p>
                <p>Brief explanations of each data point shown in the on-screen report may be viewed by hovering your mouse over their titles at any time.</p>
                <p>You may open this guide at any time by pressing the blue information icon in the upper right corner.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <a
                    class="btn btn-success got-it"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    data-dismiss="modal"
                    >Got it, thanks!</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="fade hide modal" id="aks-qsg">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <button
                    class="close"
                    type="button"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    data-dismiss="modal"
                    >&times;</button>
                <h3>New User Guide</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <p>This tool grabs keywords that are currently being searched for on Amazon. The data obtained via this tool is extremely valuable because it alllows you to put your products directly in front of your target audience.</p>
                <p>For best results with Kindle marketing, grab a list of keywords from phrases that interest you and then analyze them in the Kindle Niche Analyzer.</p>
                <p>Eliminate the guesswork with Zon Keyword Sidekick.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <a
                    class="btn btn-success got-it"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    data-dismiss="modal"
                    >Got it, thanks!</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="fade hide modal" id="ps">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <button
                    class="close"
                    type="button"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    data-dismiss="modal"
                    >&times;</button>
                <h3>How do we know this?</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <p>
                    Each hour, we scan Amazon for user searches similar to
                    phrases such as "books like..." and "books similar to..."
                    to find out what people want to read more of, right now.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We then identify these products and show them to you here
                    so that you have an immediate understanding of what's
                    currently in demand.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <a
                    class="btn btn-success got-it"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    data-dismiss="modal"
                    >Got it, thanks!</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="fade hide modal" ng-controller="modal">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <button
                    class="close"
                    type="button"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    ng-click="click()"
                    >&times;</button>
                <h3>[! top !]</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body" ng-bind-html-unsafe="middle"></div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <a
                    class="btn btn-success"
                    ng-click="click()"
                    >Close</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <form
            accept-charset="UTF-8"
            action="[! action !]"
            class="hide"
            method="POST"
            ng-controller="download"
            >
            <input name="json" type="hidden" value="[! json !]">
        </form>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/jquery/jquery.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/jquery.cookie/jquery.cookie.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/bootstrap-datepicker/js/bootstrap-datepicker.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/jquery-zclip/jquery.zclip.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/angular/angular.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/bootstrap/docs/assets/js/bootstrap.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/lodash/dist/lodash.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/moment/min/moment-with-locales.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/vendor/select2/select2.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() }}{{ app.request.baseUrl }}/javascripts/all.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
    </body>
</html>
